 <h1>{{ page.title }}</h1>
	<p> 
	Welcome to the website of the Kleine seminar! This small seminar takes place at Universiteit Gent and was initiated in summer 2019 to create a space 
	for graduate students and postdoc researchers with shared research interests to study recent subject in depth. The method is quite simple:
	each semester, the members meet and decide of one subject they want to investigate, then they choose a base reference and divide the subject amongst
	themselves so that each of them will present a part. It aims to keep an informal ambiance and every kind of questions is welcomed, especially 
	<a href="https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/ask-yourself-dumb-questions-and-answer-them/">dumb ones</a>! 
	</p>


	<h4>Next meeting: June 2022, Beginning with crystal bases.</h4>
	
	<p> 
    	We will start the study of the book Crystal bases, precise schedule to follow.
	</p>
			
	<h4>Next subject: Crystal bases</h4>
	
	<p>
	The book of Daniel Bump and Anne Schilling: Crystal Bases. Representations and Combinatorics.
	</p>
	
			
	
		
